  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      That SPECT brain imaging tracks and is consistent with clinical history and physical exam as
      well as cognitive testing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study is a retrospective review of the PI's experience using SPECT brain imaging and
      hyperbaric oxygen therapy in the diagnosis and treatment of non-acute phases of carbon
      monoxide poisoning. The purpose is to see if the SPECT brain imaging is consistent with the
      clinical condition and cognitive testing on the patients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
